1) enable encoding in JSP response header
<%@ page contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8" %>
2) enable posting all in UTF-8
$CATALINA_HOME/../server.xml
Connector, add attribute URIEncoding="UTF-8"
or (Tomcat 4.1 like behaviour) useBodyEncodingForURI="true"
3) Set Struts controller default encoding in struts-config.xml
<controller contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
4) Write custom RequestProcessor to set content type for all requests
struts-config.xml:
<controller contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8"  processorClass="ru.runa.commons.web.struts.CustomRequestProcessor" />
CustomRequestProcessor.java:
public class CustomRequestProcessor extends RequestProcessor {

	protected boolean processPreprocess(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) {
		try {
			request.setCharacterEncoding("UTF-8");
			return true;
		} catch (UnsupportedEncodingException e) {
			e.printStackTrace();
			return false;
		}
	}
}

[1] http://tagunov.tripod.com/i18n/i18n.html
[2] http://www.experts-exchange.com/Web/Web_Languages/JSP/Q_20998460.html
